<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,151,2012]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,151,176]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Carapace transversely subovate, c. 
<number box="[731,766,151,175]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1.3">1.3</number>
times broader than long; dorsal carapace, lateral branchial regions markedly swollen; exorbital tooth weakly oblique, forming rounded obtuse angle posteriorly marking widest point of carapace, especially in larger specimens; front c. 
<number box="[909,958,223,247]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="0.65">0.65</number>
times carapace width, margin straight or slightly concave in dorsal view, appearing smooth but microscopically granular, with pair of low lateral swellings behind margin; supraorbital margin entire, semicircular; dorsal surface of cheliped carpus conspicuously granular; walking legs relatively short; P 
<number box="[518,532,332,356]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="4.0">4</number>
merus c. 
<number box="[640,678,332,356]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2.3">2.3</number>
times longer than wide; P 
<number box="[996,1009,332,356]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="5.0">5</number>
merus similar, 
<number box="[1196,1231,332,356]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2.4">2.4</number>
times longer; P 
<number box="[1422,1436,332,356]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="4.0">4</number>
propodus c. 
<number box="[278,316,367,391]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2.6">2.6</number>
times longer than wide; P 
<number box="[612,625,367,391]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="5.0">5</number>
merus c. 
<number box="[735,770,367,391]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2.3">2.3</number>
times; male abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[1033,1135,367,391]" captionStart="FIGURE 13. A – E" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1920,1943]" captionTargetBox="[221,1357,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[198,1376,173,1893]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 13. A – E, Chiromantes silus sp. nov., ZRC 2012.0787, holotype male (16.3 × 12.8 mm), Guam; F – J, C. leptomerus sp. nov., NMNS- 7028 - 001, holotype male (16.8 × 12.7 mm), Taiwan. A, F, male abdomen (somites 3 – 6, telson); B, G, ventral view of left G 1; C, H, dorsal view of left G 1; D, I, ventral view of distal part of left G 1; E, J, dorsal view of distal part of left G 1. All structures denuded. Scales: A – C, F – H, = 1.0 mm; D, E, I, J = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283294/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig. 
<number box="[1085,1112,367,391]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="13.0">13</number>
A
</figureCitation>
) moderately broad, somite 
<number box="[151,165,404,428]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="6.0">6</number>
with lateral margins broadly divergent with margins relatively evenly convex, somite 
<number box="[1165,1179,404,428]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="3.0">3</number>
width 
<number box="[1263,1298,404,428]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="3.2">3.2</number>
times basal width of telson; G 
<number box="[359,369,439,463]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1.0">1</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[384,516,439,463]" captionStart="FIGURE 13. A – E" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1920,1943]" captionTargetBox="[221,1357,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[198,1376,173,1893]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 13. A – E, Chiromantes silus sp. nov., ZRC 2012.0787, holotype male (16.3 × 12.8 mm), Guam; F – J, C. leptomerus sp. nov., NMNS- 7028 - 001, holotype male (16.8 × 12.7 mm), Taiwan. A, F, male abdomen (somites 3 – 6, telson); B, G, ventral view of left G 1; C, H, dorsal view of left G 1; D, I, ventral view of distal part of left G 1; E, J, dorsal view of distal part of left G 1. All structures denuded. Scales: A – C, F – H, = 1.0 mm; D, E, I, J = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283294/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig. 
<number box="[437,463,439,463]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="13.0">13</number>
B–E
</figureCitation>
) relatively slender, weakly tapering to broadly convex subdistal shoulder; distally slender, strongly bent to 
<number box="[427,457,476,500]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="45.0">45</number>
° angle; terminal process long, with dorsal margin concave, apically pointed.
</paragraph>
